 Charles Wheelan, professor at 
Dartmouth College and author of Naked Statistics: Stripping the 
Dread From the Data' says predictive analysis has become very 
important and is potentially dangerous and potentially powerful.
He also says it's not very different from what the Federal 
Reserve tries to do when forecasting the economy. Whllan talks 
with Bloomberg's Vonnie Quinn on  Bloomberg Radio 's "The Hays 
Advantage."  (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 16:26
 